The Marine Science program in the School of Ocean Science and Engineering at The University of Southern Mississippi  is growing and we are advertising for three faculty members (details available by following the announcement links).  One of these will be the third hire in our new undergraduate Ocean Engineering Program, the second is for a Biological Oceanographer, and the third is a Teaching Faculty position.

The links to the job descriptions and application instructions are given below.

Ocean Engineering (Asst./Assoc. Prof.)

https://usm.csod.com/ats/careersite/JobDetails.aspx?id=1247

Biological Oceanography (Asst. Prof)

https://usm.csod.com/ats/careersite/JobDetails.aspx?id=1255

Teaching Faculty (Asst. Prof.)

https://usm.csod.com/ats/careersite/JobDetails.aspx?id=1280 
